_Documentation for API v2 can be found_ [_here_](https://github.com/flowerchecker/Plant-id-API/wiki)_. Or see_ [_overview of changes_](https://github.com/flowerchecker/Plant-id-API/wiki/Major-changes-of-API-v3-vs-API-v2) _between versions._

[Plant.id](https://www.kindwise.com/plant-id) is a machine learning-based service to identify indoor plants, wildflowers, trees, grasses, and other plant species from images. Additionally, Plant.id can evaluate the health of plants and detect various diseases, vermins or pests. To use the API you need to [get an API key](http://admin.kindwise.com/).

To use API from **python**, use SDK: [kindwise API client](https://github.com/flowerchecker/kindwise-api-client).

### How to use this documentation

This is a description of an important part of the API. The specification of the endpoints is given below. In the right column, you can find example calls of these endpoints (on the right you can toggle between different examples).

You can also open this [documentation directly on postman](https://www.postman.com/winter-shadow-932363/workspace/kindwise/collection/24599534-c4a4048d-ed97-4532-8980-3159ddbfe629), where you can see endpoints and examples, and you can also try it out (after providing your API key).

More implementation examples can be found [here](https://github.com/flowerchecker/plant-id-examples).

[Here](https://plant.id/api/v3/openapi.yaml) is openAPI definition of this api.

## Authentication

You should provide the `Api-Key` header with your API key. You can request it [here](http://admin.kindwise.com/).

## Identification request

There are two methods to create a new identification:

-   using `application/json` request - all attributes including images are encoded in json body - see [the example](https://www.postman.com/winter-shadow-932363/workspace/kindwise/example/24599534-774e14e0-ac40-4585-9234-2536187a8bbb)

-   using `multipart/form-data` request - attributes are sent in text fields; images are sent as files - see [the example](https://www.postman.com/winter-shadow-932363/workspace/kindwise/example/24599534-edb0a630-65dc-4132-b993-896ca2bb53cc)

Attributes:

-   **`images`**

    -   `application/json`: a list of strings (required) with one or more images of the plant you want to identify of either:

        -   image(s) encoded as strings in [Base64,](https://base64.guru/converter/encode/image)
        -   public URL(s) of images

    -   `multipart/form-data` - all images in file fields (names of file fields are not important)

-   `latitude` - float (optional) - geographic coordinate, increases the identification accuracy

-   `longitude` - float (optional) - geographic coordinate, increases the identification accuracy
-   `similar_images` - boolean (optional) - if `true`, the model also selects images similar to the provided images for each suggestion
-   `custom_id` - int (optional) - a unique identifier, can be used to access the identification results
-   `datetime` - str (optional) - to improve results, e.g. for images taken at different seasons, specify the date when the images were taken in ISO format with variable precision (e.g. `2023-06-22` for days or `2023-06-22T11:28` for minutes)
-   `health` - str (optional)

    -   `only` - response contains only health assessment
    -   `auto` - the health assessment response is included only if a plant is labelled as diseased (`is_healthy=false`). The total credit depends on whether health assessment is returned (**2 credits**) or not (**1 credit**).
    -   `all` - response contains both plant species classification and health assessment; for such identification, **2 credits** are charged (1 for taxa classification and 1 for health assessment)

-   `suggestion_filter` - dict (optional) in format `{"classification": "FILTER_NAME (filter examples below)"}` - restricts the output of the model to specified list of classes (taxonomy, region or plant type) and adjusts the probabilities. The lists can be combined with logical operators and parentheses. The lists are available [here](https://plant.id/suggestion_filters). Examples:

    -   Vegetables - `{"classification": "vegetable"}`
    -   Houseplants and wild plants in Europe - `{"classification": "houseplant OR continent__europe"}`
    -   Trees in Europe and North America - `{"classification": "(continent__northern_america OR continent__europe) AND tree"}`

-   `classification_level` - str (optional) - classification model can give plant identification at 3 levels of taxonomy: genus, species and infraspecies (includes cultivars, subspecies, varieties and trademarks). This attribute allows to adjust which type of taxon is presented in response.

    -   `species` - **default** - suggested plants are genus and species
    -   `all` - suggested plants are genus, species and infraspecies
    -   `genus` - suggested plants are only genus

-   `classification_raw` - bool (optional) - if `true`, suggestions of classification are kept in 3 original taxonomy levels (genus, species and infraspecies), without postprocessing. Please note that the response structure is changed, see the [example](https://www.postman.com/winter-shadow-932363/workspace/kindwise/example/24599534-7ea4e714-093e-4f0b-b435-58dcbe587f0b).

-   `symptoms` - bool (optional) - if `true,` returns heatmaps (as base64 images) and severity score for each identified disease symptom, and an overall defect score, see the [example](https://winter-shadow-932363.postman.co/workspace/Kindwise-private~84148215-9fd3-4627-8ef5-00f8bb91dcd1/example/25263203-b1934264-e4a2-4758-be9b-76dfb6ab061e?action=share&creator=25263203&ctx=documentation).

## Identification result

Here we comment on important parts of the result. For a complete example of the results see the response examples below.

-   `access_token` - a unique identifier of the identification, can be used to access the identification results
-   `result`\->`is_plant` - prediction of the model about presence of a plant in the input image; see [this collection](https://plant.id/collection/wpusgmjyeDCXfXr) for examples

    -   `binary` - if `false`, image probably does not contain a plant
    -   `probability` - likelihood that image contains a plant

-   `result`\->`classification`\->`suggestions` - predictions of the model containing [taxa](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Taxon) (genus or species) suggestions and additional information; each `suggestion` consists of:
    -   `id` - the id of the suggested taxon, which doesn't change over time
    -   `name` - the name of the [taxon](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Taxon) in our database (this name can change over time)
    -   `probability` - the level of certainty that suggested taxon is the one in the image
    -   `similar_images` - if `similar_images=true` is in request, list of representative images of the identified plant is returned; the images are selected to resemble the input image; they may contain license data that should be cited when using the image
    -   `details` - additional info you requested, see below

## Health assessment result

If you have used a `health` attribute in the request or used the `health_assessment` endpoint, you will also receive health assessment results. For a full example of the results, see the response examples below.

-   `result`\->`is_healthy` - prediction of the model about the health of the plant in the input images

    -   `binary` - if `true` images are likely to contain a healthy plant
    -   `probability` - probability that images contain a healthy plant

-   `result`\->`disease` -> `suggestions`\- predictions of the model include disease suggestions and additional information; each `suggestion` consists of:

    -   `id` - the id of the suggested disease, which doesn't change over time
    -   `name` - the name of the disease in our database (this name can change over time)
    -   `probability` - the degree of certainty that the suggested disease is the one in the image
    -   `redundant` - sometimes present in suggestion (with value `true`), indicates that suggestion can be discarded, because difference between the predicted probabilities of the parent and child classes is insignificant. In other words, if the child class probability is at least 80% of the parent class probability (or within two percentage points for probabilities below 10%)
    -   `similar_images` - if `similar_images=true` is in request, list of representative images of the identified plant is returned; the images are selected to resemble the input image; they may contain license data that should be cited when using the image
    -   `details` - additional information you requested, see below

-   `result`\->`disease` -> `question`\- follow-up questions designed to differentiate between the suggestions of the model (can be `null` when no question is needed). See [this article](https://www.kindwise.com/post/new-plant-health-feature-follow-up-questions) for details.
    -   `text` - selected question
    -   `options` - one of the model's suggestions for `yes` and `no` answers (with `suggestion_index`, `entity_id` and `name` referring to the list of disease suggestions)

## Details

There is a list of additional information about plant that you can get in identification result. To get specific information, include the detail's name in the GET parameters.

The default language is English; to get details in a different language include the language parameter in the GET parameters. ISO 639 two-letter language codes are used, except for Simplified Chinese (`zh`) and Traditional Chinese (`zh-hant`).

If a certain detail is unavailable, `null` is returned.

Some details are **licensed**. If you want to use this detail, you should also cite the source.

⚠️ We are not liable for damages or injury caused by actions based on inaccurate, misleading, incomplete or wrong information provided.

This is a basic description of the available details. To see examples of return values and their exact format, see [this example](https://www.postman.com/winter-shadow-932363/workspace/kindwise/example/24599534-6b255bc8-d037-49a3-852e-82ca9cf00041) (for [health assessment](https://www.postman.com/winter-shadow-932363/workspace/kindwise/example/24599534-cd90efd7-97f2-4258-8b2f-4188cf392be6)) with all details for a single language or [this example](https://www.postman.com/winter-shadow-932363/workspace/kindwise/example/24599534-b8a81cd0-592c-44cf-b7b7-a317eb1ca1b0) with multiple languages.

### Taxa classification

-   **`common_names`** - list of strings - _localized_ - local, non-scientific name
-   **`url`** - string - _localized_ - link to plant profile page (usually Wikipedia); if localized page not available, an English one is provided
-   **`description`** - string - _localized, with license_ - short description from Wikipedia
-   **`description_gpt`** - string - _localized_ - short description from GPT
-   **`description_all`** - string - _localized, some with license_ - short description, combined Wikipedia and GPT. [Read more](https://kindwise.com/handbook#insect_descriptions).
-   **`taxonomy`** - dict - scientific taxonomy
-   **`name_authority`** - string - scientific name of the plant and authority, for example, Taraxacum officinale F.H.Wigg.
-   **`rank`** - string - taxonomic rank
-   **`gbif_id`** - int - id in [GBIF database](https://www.gbif.org/)
-   **`inaturalist_id`** - int - id in [iNaturalist database](https://www.inaturalist.org/)
-   **`image`** - string - _with licence_ - url of representative image
-   **`images`** - list - _with licences_ - list of more urls of representative images
-   **`synonyms`** - list - other names of the plant
-   **`edible_parts`** - list - edible/medicinal parts of the plant; read more in the [Handbook](https://www.kindwise.com/handbook#edible_medicinal)
-   **`propagation_methods`** - list - propagation methods of the plant (eg. seeds, cuttings...); read more in the [Handbook](https://www.kindwise.com/handbook#propagation).
-   **`watering`** - dict - minimum and maximum of how wet environment the plant prefers; read more in the [Handbook](https://www.kindwise.com/handbook#watering)
-   **`best_watering`** - string - short paragraph on optimal watering practices, English only
-   **`best_light_condition`** - string - short paragraph on optimal lighting, English only
-   **`best_soil_type`** - string - short paragraph on optimal soil types for growing the plant, English only
-   **`common uses`** - string - short paragraph on how the plant can be used, English only
-   **`toxicity`** - string - short paragraph on whether the plant is poisonous to humans or animals, English only
-   **`cultural_significance`** - string - short paragraph on the importance of the plant in human culture, English only
-   **`gpt`** - list - categories to which the plant belongs to. They can include taxonomy, region or plant type. The lists are available [here](https://plant.id/suggestion_filters). They are generated by ChatGPT.

### Diseases

-   **`local_name`** - string - _localized_ - name
-   **`description`** - string - _localized_ - short disease description compiled from Wikipedia
-   **`url`** - string - _localized_ - link to disease profile page (usually Wikipedia); if localized page not available, an English one is provided
-   **`treatment`** - dict - treatments and prevention for diseases. Not AI-generated but carefully compiled by a domain expert. Biological or chemical treatments for the disease may not be present for all diseases, but prevention is always present. Read more in the [Handbook](https://www.kindwise.com/handbook#treatment).
-   **`classification`** - list - class hierarchy of the disease, sorted from most general to the most specific
-   **`common_names`** - list - common names of the disease
-   **`cause`** - string - scientific name of the cause of the disease

The available languages are: English - `en`, German - `de`, Czech - `cs`, Spanish - `es`, French - `fr`, Italian - `it`, Dutch - `nl`, Polish - `pl`, Swedish - `sv`, Simplified Chinese - `zh`, Traditional Chinese - `zh-hant`, Danish - `da`, Turkish - `tr`, Hindi - `hi`, Arabic - `ar`, Brazilian Portuguese - `pt-BR`, Korean - `ko`.

## Response codes

| **Response code** | **Explanation**                                      |
| ----------------- | ---------------------------------------------------- |
| 200               | Succesful request                                    |
| 201               | Identification created                               |
| 400               | Invalid input data - check error message for details |
| 401               | Invalid API key                                      |
| 404               | Object not found, e.g. identification, conversation  |
| 429               | No enough credits                                    |
| 500               | Server error, try again or contact support           |

## Endpoints

### POST Create identification

https://plant.id/api/v3/identification

Send images for identification. See above for description of response and request body.

AUTHORIZATION API Key

This request is using API Key from collection[Plant.id v3](https://documenter.getpostman.com/view/24599534/2s93z5A4v2#auth-info-c4a4048d-ed97-4532-8980-3159ddbfe629)

PARAMS

details - common_names,url,description,taxonomy,rank,gbif_id,inaturalist_id,image,synonyms,edible_parts,watering,propagation_methods
comma separetad list of requested plant details (optional) see detail description above

language - en
two-letter [ISO 639-1 language code](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/List_of_ISO_639-1_codes) (optional, default `en`) - language of localized plant details can be multiple (up to 3), separated by comma - i.e. (`en,de,sv`)

async - true
boolean (optional) - if `true`: request does not wait for identification to complete and response does not contain `result` section; result can be later retrieved by next endpoint

Bodyraw (json)

```json
{
	"images": [
		"data:image/jpg;base64,"
	],
	"latitude": 49.207,
	"longitude": 16.608,
	"similar_images": true
}
```

example request:

```dart
var headers = {
  'Api-Key': 'your_api_key',
  'Content-Type': 'application/json'
};
var request = http.Request('POST', Uri.parse('https://plant.id/api/v3/identification'));
request.body = json.encode({
  "images": [
    "data:image/jpg;base64,"
  ],
  "latitude": 49.207,
  "longitude": 16.608,
  "similar_images": true
});
request.headers.addAll(headers);

http.StreamedResponse response = await request.send();

if (response.statusCode == 200) {
  print(await response.stream.bytesToString());
}
else {
  print(response.reasonPhrase);
}

```

### POST Health assessment

https://plant.id/api/v3/health\_assessment?details=local\_name,description,url,treatment,classification,common\_names,cause

Send images for health assessment. This endpoint is same as `/identification` with parameter `"health": "only"`.

AUTHORIZATIONAPI Key

This request is using API Key from collection[Plant.id v3](https://documenter.getpostman.com/view/24599534/2s93z5A4v2#auth-info-c4a4048d-ed97-4532-8980-3159ddbfe629)

PARAMS

language - en
two-letter [ISO 639-1 language code](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/List_of_ISO_639-1_codes) (optional, default `en`) - language of localized plant details can be multiple (up to 3), separated by comma - i.e. (`en,de,sv`)

async - true
boolean (optional) - if `true`: request does not wait for identification to complete and response does not contain `result` section; result can be later retrieved by next endpoint

full_disease_list - true
boolean (optional) - if `true`: list of suggested diseases contains also general diseases such as "Abiotic"

details - local_name,description,url,treatment,classification,common_names,cause
comma separetad list of requested disease details (optional) see detail description above

Bodyraw (json)

```json
{
	"images": [
		"data:image/jpeg;base64,"
	],
	"latitude": 49.207,
	"longitude": 16.608,
	"similar_images": true
}
```

example request

```dart
var headers = {
  'Api-Key': 'your_api_key',
  'Content-Type': 'application/json'
};
var request = http.Request('POST', Uri.parse('https://plant.id/api/v3/health_assessment'));
request.body = json.encode({
  "images": [
    "data:image/jpeg;base64,"
  ],
  "latitude": 49.207,
  "longitude": 16.608,
  "similar_images": true
});
request.headers.addAll(headers);

http.StreamedResponse response = await request.send();

if (response.statusCode == 200) {
  print(await response.stream.bytesToString());
}
else {
  print(response.reasonPhrase);
}
```

### GET Retrieve identification

https://plant.id/api/v3/identification/:access\_token

Can be used to

-   retrieve identification result when identification is created with `async=True`
-   retrieve past identifications (available for 6 months)
-   retrieve identification results with different details or languages

AUTHORIZATIONAPI Key

This request is using API Key from collection[Plant.id v3](https://documenter.getpostman.com/view/24599534/2s93z5A4v2#auth-info-c4a4048d-ed97-4532-8980-3159ddbfe629)

PARAMS

details - common_names,url,description,taxonomy,rank,gbif_id,inaturalist_id,image,synonyms,edible_parts,watering,propagation_methods
comma separetad list of requested plant details (optional) see detail description above

language - en
two-letter [ISO 639-1 language code](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/List_of_ISO_639-1_codes) (optional, default `en`) - language of localized plant details can be multiple (up to 3), separated by comma - i.e. (`en,de,sv`)

PATH VARIABLES

access_token - pYuv64JSAvod18b
`access_token` retrieved on identification creation (or provided `custom_id`)

example request

```dart
var headers = {
  'Api-Key': 'your_api_key',
  'Content-Type': 'application/json'
};
var request = http.Request('GET', Uri.parse('https://plant.id/api/v3/identification/AxDT9RawIwfX3fT?details=common_names,url,description,taxonomy,rank,gbif_id,inaturalist_id,image,synonyms,edible_parts,watering &language=en'));

request.headers.addAll(headers);

http.StreamedResponse response = await request.send();

if (response.statusCode == 200) {
  print(await response.stream.bytesToString());
}
else {
  print(response.reasonPhrase);
}
```

200 OK

### POST Send feedback

https://plant.id/api/v3/identification/:access\_token/feedback

Can be used to send a user feedback to an identification.

Specifics:

-   data must be in the form of JSON
-   recommended structure is either `rating` - a number from 0-5 or `comment` - a text comment from the user. Or include both
-   We will attach feedback to identification and it will be returned in next retrieve of identification.

Feedback can help us improve our model, so thank you for sending it.

AUTHORIZATION API Key
This request is using API Key from collection[Plant.id v3](https://documenter.getpostman.com/view/24599534/2s93z5A4v2#auth-info-c4a4048d-ed97-4532-8980-3159ddbfe629)

PATH VARIABLES
access_token
`access_token` retrieved on identification creation (or provided `custom_id`)

example request

```dart
var headers = {
  'Api-Key': 'your_api_key',
  'Content-Type': 'application/json'
};
var request = http.Request('POST', Uri.parse('https://plant.id/api/v3/identification/:access_token/feedback'));
request.body = json.encode({
  "rating": 5,
  "comment": "Identified poisonous plant, saved my cat! Thanks."
});
request.headers.addAll(headers);

http.StreamedResponse response = await request.send();

if (response.statusCode == 200) {
  print(await response.stream.bytesToString());
}
else {
  print(response.reasonPhrase);
}
```

200 OK

Example Response

```
{
  "message": "Feedback submitted successfully."
}
```

### GET Plants search

https://plant.id/api/v3/kb/plants/name\_search?q=aloe vera

This endpoint is alpha beta testing and **can change**!

Search plant knowledge base by query. Plants are searchable by scientific names, common names (in specified language), synonyms.

Plant name and query are always matched from start of a word., i.e. "Aloe vera" is searchable by "Aloe", "Alo", "Vera", "ver", "Aloe vera"...

AUTHORIZATIONAPI Key
This request is using API Key from collection[Plant.id v3](https://documenter.getpostman.com/view/24599534/2s93z5A4v2#auth-info-c4a4048d-ed97-4532-8980-3159ddbfe629)

PARAMS
limit - 10
int (optional) - maximum of returned result, max. 20, default 10

language - en
two-letter [ISO 639-1 language code](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/List_of_ISO_639-1_codes) (optional, default `en`) - language of common names can be multiple (up to 3), separated by comma - i.e. (`en,de,sv`)

thumbnails - true
bool (optional) - add for each result 64x64 thumbnail encoded as base64 image

example request

```dart
var headers = {
  'Api-Key': 'your_api_key',
  'Content-Type': 'application/json'
};
var request = http.Request('GET', Uri.parse('https://plant.id/api/v3/kb/plants/name_search?q=aloe vera'));

request.headers.addAll(headers);

http.StreamedResponse response = await request.send();

if (response.statusCode == 200) {
  print(await response.stream.bytesToString());
}
else {
  print(response.reasonPhrase);
}
```

200 OK

Example Response
